last_episode_to_air.name: More Than Zero
last_episode_to_air.overview: Dr. Quest travels to a Venetian mansion to authenticate the claims and machinery of paranormal scientists. The situation turns dire when the machine accidentally empowers a malevolent entity.

name: The Real Adventures of Jonny Quest
original_name: The Real Adventures of Jonny Quest
overview: The Real Adventures of Jonny Quest is an American animated action-adventure television series.

episodes.name: The Darkest Fathoms
episodes.overview: Centuries ago, ruthless pirate Black Jack Lee rode The Ivory Web to the Bermuda sea floor. When oil explorers are assaulted by a ghost ship under his apparent captaincy, Dr. Quest prepares the Questor for an investigation.

episodes.name: Escape to Questworld
episodes.overview: Race is hired to contain a nerve gas leak in Chicago, the legacy of a botched raid on Dr. Jeremiah Surd years earlier. When he and Dr. Quest are trapped, it's up to Jonny, Jessie, and Hadji to find the renegade scientist.

episodes.name: In the Realm of the Condor
episodes.overview: The Quest team follows Estella Scheele to find her missing ornithologist grandfather, and ends up finding the lost golden city of El Dorado.

episodes.name: Rage's Burning Wheel
episodes.overview: When Ezekiel Rage hijacks a space shuttle commanded by Dr. Quest and Hadji, Jonny and Jessie must stop Rage's minions who have taken over Mission Control.

episodes.name: Ndovu's Last Journey
episodes.overview: Jonny, Jessie and Hadji track an elephant, Ndovu, as it returns to the elephants' graveyard. They bump into poachers on the way there, who are determined to kill Ndovu right away.

episodes.name: Manhattan Maneater
episodes.overview: A tiger is loose in the Big Apple, and the Quest team must track it down, through subway tunnels, located underground.

episodes.name: East of Zanzibar
episodes.overview: The Quest Team enjoy a trip to the Indian Ocean to discover if there are really sea monsters roaming the seas, leading to multiple mysterious ship disappearances in the Seychelles.

episodes.name: Assault on Questworld
episodes.overview: With Benton Quest and Race Bannon attending a phenomenology conference in the Himalayas, Jonny and Jessie are forced to impersonate their fathers in Questworld when Jeremiah Surd launches a two-pronged attack on the Quest compound - and Hadji's mind.

episodes.name: Ezekiel Rage
episodes.overview: A man named Ezekiel Rage seeks vengeance because of the tragic loss of his family in a covert operation when he was a government agent. And the Quest Team gets in his way...

episodes.name: Alien in Washington
episodes.overview: Extraterrestrial transmissions turn out to be warnings to stop a series of space experiments, and the Vice President turns out to be an alien.

episodes.name: Return of the Anasazi
episodes.overview: Holding an Anasazi beacon capable of calling the alien fathers of current technology, Alice Starseer is pursued by men in black and asks Dr. Quest for help, whose capture provokes a cross-country rescue by Jonny and Jessie.

episodes.name: The Alchemist
episodes.overview: Dr. Quest is commissioned to find the Philosopher's Stone, which is reputed to turn dross to gold. When he succeeds in capturing the object, he donates it to the museum. It is stolen by Quest's partner, who wants to try it out for himself.

episodes.name: Trouble on the Colorado
episodes.overview: Alice Starseer returns to Earth to lay her grandfather to rest. But Jeremiah Surd is determined to find out what she's learned.

episodes.name: In the Wake of Mary Celeste
episodes.overview: A century ago, the cargo ship Mary Celeste sank under mysterious circumstances. While on an expedition to find the Mary Celeste's remains, Dr Quest discovers what look like crop circles at the bottom of the Sargasso Sea--and a graveyard of ships in an area barren of marine life.

episodes.name: AMOK
episodes.overview: On an archaeological expedition in Borneo, the Quest team run into a giant creature, reputed to savagely attack from all directions at the same time.

episodes.name: Besieged in Paradise
episodes.overview: Jeremiah Surd taps into and gains control of the cetacean communications internet, prodding cetaceans worldwide into savage attacks; the Quest team enlists the help of Captain Havell to stop his plan.

episodes.name: The Spectre of the Pine Barrens
episodes.overview: Dr. Quest, Jonny and Hadji head to New Jersey to investigate the Jersey Devil. Then they run into a two-hundred-year-old feud between descendants of the Redcoats and the Minutemen over the original copy of the Declaration of Independence.

episodes.name: Heroes
episodes.overview: Surd lures Jonny into a labyrinth of horrors, after stealing the Apollo statue, which was reassembled by Dr. Quest.

episodes.name: The Ballad of Belle Bonnet
episodes.overview: In the Old West, the thief Belle Bonnet stole a wagonload of gold to help an Indian school stay open, but both thief and gold were lost in vast caverns under the American desertâ€”until the Quests took the case.

episodes.name: In the Darkness of the Moon
episodes.overview: A werewolf attack in the Yukon brings a Quest team investigation to the home of a humanitarian doctor; the light of the moon illuminates both danger and mystery as the hunt begins.

episodes.name: The Secret of the MOAI
episodes.overview: A missing link is found in an alien spaceship that landed on Easter Island. But when Dr. Quest and Race enter Questworld to investigate what they've found, they run into Jeremiah Surd - who wants to experiment with human de-evolution.

episodes.name: Expedition to Khumbu
episodes.overview: Dr. Quest is missing while on an expedition to find the Yeti. Jonny and his friends head to the Himalayas to find him, but run into another scientist who's determined to bring back the Yeti.

episodes.name: Ice Will Burn
episodes.overview: While trying to reach Northern Siberia to backup the Quest Team, her plane crashes and she discovers a colony of ancient Russians underground.

episodes.name: Future Rage
episodes.overview: Ezekiel Rage steals a compact nuclear device and plans to blow up the polar ice caps. The Aurora Borealis holds the key to stopping him.

episodes.name: Alligators and Okeechobee Vikings
episodes.overview: The Quest Team discovers that criminals were using Alligators to break into a drilling factory in the Florida Everglades when they were investigating the case using an ornate Viking Sword that the Alligators left behind.

episodes.name: To Bardo and Back
episodes.overview: The Quest team employs QuestWorld to try and revive Race, who has been rendered comatose in a rodeo accident caused by Jeremiah Surd -- who in turn exploits the opportunity to attack Race at his most vulnerable.

episodes.name: The Mummies of Malenque
episodes.overview: During an expedition with Jessie's mother Estella, the Quest team discovers a plague that wiped out an ancient Inca-like tribe.

episodes.name: Rock of Rages
episodes.overview: Journeying to the Czech Republic to translate an artefact, which holds the key to controlling a Golen, the Quest Team bump into an ex-KGB operative who's determined to reactivate the Golem to overthrow the government.

episodes.name: Bloodlines
episodes.overview: A memory of Pasha sends Hadji to Calcutta to search for his real father to figure out the truth of his past.

episodes.name: Race Against Danger
episodes.overview: Race has to cross an obstacle course where he set the record for Special Forces recruits -- but there've been some modifications since he was last there.

episodes.name: The Dark Mountain
episodes.overview: The Quest team believes that the Canadian legend - Bigfoot is roaming in the Quest compound stealing electronic devices. They try to find out what is going on as hunters bag themselves an exotic trophy.

episodes.name: Cyberswitch
episodes.overview: The insane Surd finds a way to switch bodies with Race and is ready to go on a rampage using his new identity. And now it is easier for him to kill Benton Quest (who can reverse the process).

episodes.name: Undersea Urgency
episodes.overview: A seaquake releases a horde of murderous amphibians on a nearly-completed underwater research facility.

episodes.name: Nemesis
episodes.overview: The nefarious Dr. Zin subverts a satellite designed by Benton Quest and uses it to hold the world for ransom.

episodes.name: DNA Doomsday
episodes.overview: During a simulation to test out a military installation's defences, a bio-computer is out of control.

episodes.name: Ghost Quest
episodes.overview: En route to Nova Scotia in the newly christened Questor II, Jonny, Jessie and Hadji come upon a fog-enveloped island with a tragic history.

episodes.name: Nuclear Netherworld
episodes.overview: Jonny and Hadji discovers a nearby biodome experiment is really a cover for a plant making uranium casted weapons when they visited Jonny's Grandpa, Doug Wildey on his ranch.

episodes.name: Eclipse
episodes.overview: When Hadji rescues a beautiful girl in New Orleans, she exerts a strange influence over him.

episodes.name: Without a Trace
episodes.overview: Air Force One vanishes with the president within it, and all the evidence points to Benton Quest and Race Bannon. Jonny, Jessie and Hadji must elude government agents to prove their fathers' innocence by finding the real culprit.

episodes.name: Village of the Doomed
episodes.overview: In a father-son bonding trip in Devon, Benton and Jonny head to the big pond to fish but on the way, they come across an idyllic little village that's just a little too peaceful.

episodes.name: Dark Sentinel
episodes.overview: The Quest Team help a scientist harvest life-giving sap from trees that are being threatened by a logging operation in Cameroon.

episodes.name: Other Space
episodes.overview: Scientists are working on transdimensional technology that will help them open a portal to another dimension - and its denizens, who waste no time staking their claim on Earth.

episodes.name: Digital Doublecross
episodes.overview: When Jonny and Jessie challenge each other to a Virtual Reality game in Questworld, Surd intervenes with a challenge of his own.

episodes.name: Thoughtscape
episodes.overview: Jonny and Benton venture into Jessie's mind to undo Surd's malicious attempt to strike at the Quest team from within - but it turns out that Jessie can take care of herself.

episodes.name: The Bangalore Falcon
episodes.overview: While touring Bangalore, Jonny, Jessie and Hadji find a rare falcon, reputedly from a hidden realm that appears once every 500 years - a realm whose river's water is said to bestow immortality. A beautiful ornithologist is also very interested in the bird; but is she who she says she is?

episodes.name: Diamonds and Jade
episodes.overview: Travelling to Indonesia to help an old friend recover a precious jewel, Race, Jonny and Jessie discover it is protected by a supernatural force.

episodes.name: The Edge of Yesterday
episodes.overview: Ezekiel Rage plants a nuclear bomb in the bowels of Earth and Jonny and Jessie must revert back into time to stop his evil deed.

episodes.name: The Haunted Sonata
episodes.overview: On a visit to the Czech Republic, Jonny and Jessie encounter a ghostly apparition that leads them to an incomplete sonata -- and a generations-old secret.

episodes.name: General Winter
episodes.overview: General Vostok returns with the weapon that defeated Napoleon and he wants Benton to make it bigger and more powerful.

episodes.name: Night of the Zinja
episodes.overview: After the death of Dr. Zin, his two daughters are determined to carry on the Zin dynasty by destroying all the members of the Quest Team.

episodes.name: The Robot Spies
episodes.overview: Dr. Zin launches the ultimate plan to defeat the Quests.

episodes.name: More Than Zero
episodes.overview: Dr. Quest travels to a Venetian mansion to authenticate the claims and machinery of paranormal scientists. The situation turns dire when the machine accidentally empowers a malevolent entity.
